    <section class="story">
      <p>Meera, a schoolteacher from a rural town, struggled to manage her family’s expenses on a modest income. Monthly bills, unexpected medical expenses, and school fees often left her in debt. One day, she downloaded a personal finance app offering multilingual support.</p>

      <h2>How Meera Used the App:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Expense Tracking:</strong> She recorded daily expenses with voice input, making it easier to stay consistent.</li>
        <li><strong>Budgeting Tools:</strong> The app helped Meera categorize her spending, revealing that she spent a significant amount on unnecessary groceries.</li>
        <li><strong>Savings Recommendations:</strong> The app suggested ways to cut costs and build savings, including reducing unnecessary spending and setting a target savings amount.</li>
        <li><strong>Recurring Deposits:</strong> She linked the app to a recurring deposit account, automating savings.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Results After Six Months:</h2>
      <p>By making small changes and following the app's recommendations, Meera was able to save ₹20,000 in six months. She achieved her goal of having enough funds to support her daughter’s education and her family's long-term security.</p>

      <h2>Takeaway:</h2>
      <p>Small changes and financial awareness can have a huge impact on achieving financial stability and peace of mind.</p>
